                                                                  GIT-BRANCHING

 1> Main Branch = the main branch is the primary and stable version of a project.
                
                  it contain the latest working code.


 2> Branch = A branch is an independent copy of a project.
 where developers can work on new feature or bug fixes without affecting the mainj branches

              
 3> Why do we use branches ? 

   #> keep main branch safe.
   #> develop new features independently.
   #> fix bugs without affecting the stable project.
   #> allow multiple developers to work simultaneously.

 4>  git branch 'branch-name' = for create new branch.


 5> git branch = view all branch in repostitory.


 6> git switch 'branch name' = swith from one branch to another.
           
          or
  git checkout 'branch name'



